le and appropriate, thus making it relevant for anthropological and linguistic theory and practice, as well as for folklore and literary criticism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFigures of speech. 0aJoking. 0aPlays on words. 0aRiddles. 0aWord games. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292796690423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292796690/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK